    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Japanese porcelain produced in the Arita district of Hizen province by the Sakaida family during the Tokugawa period. Wares were generally of hexagonal, octagonal, or square shape. They initially featured an underglaze blue-and-white, and later a polychrome overglaze technique.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
